<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><template xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns="openEHR/v1/Template" xmlns:uuid="java:java.util.UUID"><id>aa651b60-3947-4ddc-a98f-531033bf1eba</id><name>Diagnostic Imaging - Magnetic Resonance - MR Abdomen Angiography Order</name><description><lifecycle_state>Initial</lifecycle_state><details><purpose>For ordering a(n) MR Abdomen Angiography</purpose><use/><misuse/></details><other_details><item><key>MetaDataSet:Sample Set </key><value>Template metadata sample set </value></item><item><key>Acknowledgements</key><value/></item><item><key>Business Process Level</key><value/></item><item><key>Care setting</key><value/></item><item><key>Client group</key><value/></item><item><key>Clinical Record Element</key><value/></item><item><key>Copyright</key><value/></item><item><key>Issues</key><value/></item><item><key>Owner</key><value/></item><item><key>Sign off</key><value/></item><item><key>Speciality</key><value/></item><item><key>User roles</key><value/></item></other_details></description><annotations path="[openEHR-EHR-INSTRUCTION.service_request.v1]"><items><item><key>Imaging.Body Part</key><value>%=AB</value></item><item><key>Imaging.Laterality</key><value>No</value></item><item><key>Catalogue Pattern.Patient Requirements</key><value>Laboratory: Creatinine LEVEL and eGFR required within three months of exam. Required for patients with known or suspected renal impairment/failure.;Medications: Patient cooperative/able to hold still with appropriate pain management and oral sedation as required. Discontinue medications running through pumps prior to MRI procedure. If pumps are unable to be discontinued, please contact the MRI department for further instructions. Continue oral medications as ordered.;IV requirements: Venous access required, infusion pump disconnected. Contact MRI department if this is not possible.</value></item><item><key>Catalogue Pattern.Clinical Communication</key><value>Inpatient Clinical Communication:  MRI Patient History, Screening Form and signed consent form (if required) to be completed by patient, family member or designate and sent via fax to the MRI department prior to patient arrival. If the patient is unable to complete screening form and/or give consent independently, ensure that a legal procedure consent form is provided and contact MRI department for further instructions. Patient in hospital attire with no metal pins, buttons or fasteners. The patient must remove all metal items before coming to the MRI department. This includes pins, hairpieces, jewellery, makeup, prostheses, wallets or phones. The patient may keep their glasses, false teeth, and hearing aids but these will be removed prior to the MRI exam.  Complete patient chart, including current medication record, must accompany patient to the MRI department. If required for interpretation/translation, patient safety, or comfort, family members accompanying patients will be required to complete the MRI screening form in the MRI department.  Nursing accompaniment if required. Pediatric: Parent/legal guardian should accompany the patient.; Outpatient Clinical Communication:  MRI patient history, screening form and signed consent form (if required) to be completed by patient, family member or designate at the time of appointment. Pre screening questions will also be completed by physician at the time of the request, this will then be updated/validated by patient or legal designate at the time of the appointment. If the patient is unable to complete screening form and/or give consent independently, ensure that a legal designate is available at the time of the procedure to provide consent or has coordinated with the MRI department prior to appointment. Patient to change into hospital attire with no metal pins, buttons or fasteners prior to the MRI exam.  Patient to remove all metal items, includes pins, hairpieces, jewellery, makeup, prostheses, wallets or phones. The patient may keep their glasses, false teeth, and hearing aids but these will be removed prior to the MRI exam. If required for interpretation/translation, patient safety, or comfort, family members may accompany patients to assist with the completion of the MRI screening form. Nursing accompaniment if required. Pediatric: Parent/legal guardian should accompany the patient.</value></item><item><key>Catalogue Pattern.Synonyms</key><value>MRA Abdomen</value></item><item><key>Catalogue Pattern.Resources </key><value>http://insite.albertahealthservices.ca/assets/policy/clp-di-prov-dimr3-0-gad-admin-renal-impair.pdf</value></item></items></annotations><definition xsi:type="INSTRUCTION" archetype_id="openEHR-EHR-INSTRUCTION.service_request.v1" concept_name="Service request" max="1" name="MR Abdomen Angiography"/><integrity_checks xsi:type="ArchetypeIntegrity" archetype_id="openEHR-EHR-INSTRUCTION.service_request.v1"><digest id="MD5-CAM-1.0.1">B48161A11EF4549FFAE82EE73B385AF5</digest></integrity_checks><integrity_checks xsi:type="ArchetypeIntegrity" archetype_id="openEHR-EHR-CLUSTER.service_request_information.v1"><digest id="MD5-CAM-1.0.1">230A8D964017E1FD7AC82EBDEE0202A6</digest></integrity_checks></template>